{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":620,"text":"When we think about mapping cities,"},{"time":2395,"text":"we tend to think about roads\nand streets and buildings,"},{"time":5200,"text":"and the settlement narrative\nthat led to their creation,"},{"time":8000,"text":"or you might think about\nthe bold vision of an urban designer,"},{"time":10984,"text":"but there's other ways\nto think about mapping cities"},{"time":13487,"text":"and how they got to be made."},{"time":15653,"text":"Today, I want to show you\na new kind of map."},{"time":17746,"text":"This is not a geographic map."},{"time":19242,"text":"This is a map of the relationships \nbetween people in my hometown"},{"time":22373,"text":"of Baltimore, Maryland,"},{"time":23713,"text":"and what you can see here is that\neach dot represents a person,"},{"time":28130,"text":"each line represents a relationship\nbetween those people,"},{"time":31424,"text":"and each color represents a community\nwithin the network."}]},{"cues":[{"time":34870,"text":"Now, I'm here on the green side,\ndown on the far right where the geeks are,"},{"time":39732,"text":"and TEDx also is down \non the far right. (Laughter)"},{"time":43580,"text":"Now, on the other side of the network,"},{"time":46157,"text":"you tend to have primarily\nAfrican-American and Latino folks"},{"time":49117,"text":"who are really concerned about somewhat\ndifferent things than the geeks are,"},{"time":52707,"text":"but just to give some sense,"},{"time":54148,"text":"the green part of the network \nwe call Smalltimore,"},{"time":56554,"text":"for those of us that inhabit it,"},{"time":58099,"text":"because it seems as though\nwe're living in a very small town."},{"time":61014,"text":"We see the same people\nover and over again,"},{"time":63048,"text":"but that's because\nwe're not really exploring"},{"time":65219,"text":"the full depth and breadth of the city."},{"time":68081,"text":"On the other end of the network,"},{"time":69833,"text":"you have folks who are interested\nin things like hip-hop music"},{"time":72770,"text":"and they even identify with living\nin the DC/Maryland/Virginia area"},{"time":76574,"text":"over, say, the Baltimore city\ndesignation proper."},{"time":80990,"text":"But in the middle, you see that there's"},{"time":83090,"text":"something that connects\nthe two communities together,"},{"time":85573,"text":"and that's sports."},{"time":86452,"text":"We have the Baltimore Orioles,\nthe Baltimore Ravens football team,"},{"time":89540,"text":"Michael Phelps, the Olympian."},{"time":90986,"text":"Under Armour, you may have heard of,\nis a Baltimore company,"},{"time":93824,"text":"and that community of sports\nacts as the only bridge"},{"time":96257,"text":"between these two ends of the network."}]},{"cues":[{"time":98528,"text":"Let's take a look at San Francisco."},{"time":100423,"text":"You see something a little bit\ndifferent happening in San Francisco."},{"time":103609,"text":"On the one hand, you do have\nthe media, politics and news lobe"},{"time":108002,"text":"that tends to exist\nin Baltimore and other cities,"},{"time":110537,"text":"but you also have this\nvery predominant group"},{"time":112892,"text":"of geeks and techies that are sort of\ntaking over the top half of the network,"},{"time":117285,"text":"and there's even a group\nthat's so distinct and clear"},{"time":119787,"text":"that we can identify it\nas Twitter employees,"},{"time":122137,"text":"next to the geeks, in between\nthe gamers and the geeks,"},{"time":125504,"text":"at the opposite end\nof the hip-hop spectrum."},{"time":128445,"text":"So you can see, though,"},{"time":130162,"text":"that the tensions that we've\nheard about in San Francisco"},{"time":132843,"text":"in terms of people being\nconcerned about gentrification"},{"time":135764,"text":"and all the new tech companies\nthat are bringing new wealth"},{"time":138523,"text":"and settlement into the city are real,"},{"time":140620,"text":"and you can actually see\nthat documented here."},{"time":142849,"text":"You can see the LGBT community"},{"time":144869,"text":"is not really getting along\nwith the geek community that well,"},{"time":148165,"text":"the arts community, the music community."},{"time":150297,"text":"And so it leads to things like this."},{"time":152070,"text":"[\"Evict Twitter\"]"},{"time":153043,"text":"Somebody sent me this photo\na few weeks ago,"},{"time":154867,"text":"and it shows what is happening\non the ground in San Francisco,"},{"time":157774,"text":"and I think you can\nactually try to understand that"},{"time":160158,"text":"through looking at a map like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":161860,"text":"Let's take a look at Rio de Janeiro."},{"time":163620,"text":"I spent the last few weeks\ngathering data about Rio,"},{"time":166074,"text":"and one of the things\nthat stood out to me about this city"},{"time":168881,"text":"is that everything's\nreally kind of mixed up."},{"time":171003,"text":"It's a very heterogenous city in a way \nthat Baltimore or San Francisco is not."},{"time":175107,"text":"You still have the lobe of people involved"},{"time":177562,"text":"with government, newspapers,\npolitics, columnists."},{"time":179946,"text":"TEDxRio is down in the lower right,\nright next to bloggers and writers."},{"time":183350,"text":"But then you also have this\ntremendous diversity of people"},{"time":186059,"text":"that are interested\nin different kinds of music."},{"time":188333,"text":"Even Justin Bieber fans\nare represented here."},{"time":190537,"text":"Other boy bands, country singers,"},{"time":193429,"text":"gospel music, funk and rap\nand stand-up comedy,"},{"time":196337,"text":"and there's even a whole section\naround drugs and jokes."},{"time":199376,"text":"How cool is that?"},{"time":200862,"text":"And then the Flamengo football team\nis also represented here."},{"time":203996,"text":"So you have that same kind of spread"},{"time":206156,"text":"of sports and civics\nand the arts and music,"},{"time":208871,"text":"but it's represented\nin a very different way,"},{"time":211032,"text":"and I think that maybe fits\nwith our understanding of Rio"},{"time":214352,"text":"as being a very multicultural,\nmusically diverse city."}]},{"cues":[{"time":218366,"text":"So we have all this data."},{"time":221984,"text":"It's an incredibly rich set of data\nthat we have about cities now,"},{"time":225102,"text":"maybe even richer than any data set\nthat we've ever had before."},{"time":228348,"text":"So what can we do with it?"},{"time":230272,"text":"Well, I think the first thing\nthat we can try to understand"},{"time":233142,"text":"is that segregation is a social construct."},{"time":235480,"text":"It's something that we choose to do,\nand we could choose not to do it,"},{"time":238824,"text":"and if you kind of think about it,"},{"time":240756,"text":"what we're doing with this data\nis aiming a space telescope at a city"},{"time":244167,"text":"and looking at it as if was\na giant high school cafeteria,"},{"time":247199,"text":"and seeing how everybody arranged\nthemselves in a seating chart."},{"time":250937,"text":"Well maybe it's time to shake up\nthe seating chart a little bit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":254250,"text":"The other thing that we start to realize"},{"time":256790,"text":"is that race is a really\npoor proxy for diversity."},{"time":259428,"text":"We've got people represented\nfrom all different types of races"},{"time":262365,"text":"across the entire map here --"},{"time":264691,"text":"only looking at race"},{"time":267067,"text":"doesn't really contribute to\nour development of diversity."},{"time":269785,"text":"So if we're trying to use diversity"},{"time":271524,"text":"as a way to tackle some of our\nmore intractable problems,"},{"time":274605,"text":"we need to start to think \nabout diversity in a new way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":277899,"text":"And lastly, we have the ability to create"},{"time":281426,"text":"interventions to start to reshape\nour cities in a new way,"},{"time":284520,"text":"and I believe that if\nwe have that capability,"},{"time":287120,"text":"we may even bear some\nresponsibility to do so."}]},{"cues":[{"time":290185,"text":"So what is a city?"},{"time":291950,"text":"I think some might say that it is"},{"time":294156,"text":"a geographical area or a collection\nof streets and buildings,"},{"time":297316,"text":"but I believe that a city \nis the sum of the relationships"},{"time":300068,"text":"of the people that live there,"},{"time":301629,"text":"and I believe that if we can start to\ndocument those relationships in a real way"},{"time":307680,"text":"then maybe we have a real shot"},{"time":309413,"text":"at creating those kinds of cities\nthat we'd like to have."}]},{"cues":[{"time":312088,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":313445,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}